indifference,
that
she
had
not
really
any
dislike
to
the
scheme.
To
Pemberley,
therefore,
they
were
to
go.
Elizabeth,
as
they
drove
along,
watched
for
the
first
appearance
of
Pemberley
Woods
with
some
perturbation;
and
when
at
length
they
turned
in
at
the
lodge,
her
