my
own,
and
welcomed
to
them
as
visitors
my
uncle
and
aunt.
But
no,"
recollecting
herself
"that
could
never
be;
my
uncle
and
aunt
would
have
been
lost
to
me;
I
should
not
have
been
allowed
to
invite
them."
This
was
a
lucky
